During National Hispanic Heritage Month, President Biden honors the contributions of Latinos to the United States. He highlights the achievements of Latinos in various fields, such as healthcare, education, business, and the arts. The President emphasizes his administration's efforts to expand opportunities for Latinos, including job creation, healthcare enrollment, and education access. He also mentions initiatives focused on Puerto Rico's economic recovery and climate change. President Biden reiterates his commitment to fixing the broken immigration system and providing a pathway to citizenship for Dreamers, temporary status holders, and farm workers. He acknowledges the leadership of his Latino Cabinet members and recognizes the impact of Latinos serving the nation in different capacities. The President concludes by proclaiming September 15 through October 15 as National Hispanic Heritage Month and calls upon all Americans to celebrate Hispanic heritage and recognize its impact on the nation.